{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "We give thanks to you, God. We give thanks, for your Name is near."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Men tell about your wondrous works."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When I choose the appointed time, I will judge blamelessly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The earth and all its inhabitants quake. I firmly hold its pillars. Selah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I said to the arrogant, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Don’t boast!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I said to the wicked,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Don’t lift up the horn.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Don’t lift up your horn on high. Don’t speak with a stiff neck.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For neither from the east, nor from the west, nor yet from the south, comes exaltation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But God is the judge. He puts down one, and lifts up another."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For in Yahweh’s hand there is a cup, full of foaming wine mixed with spices. He pours it out. Indeed the wicked of the earth drink and drink it to its very dregs."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But I will declare this forever: I will sing praises to the God of Jacob."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will cut off all the horns of the wicked, but the horns of the righteous shall be lifted up."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}